user_query:
I need to generate a consistent demonstration of our model latency display using our required ping formats. Please do the following:

- Read input/ping_scenarios.json for the scenarios (structure and values also listed below for convenience).
- For each item under "single", create a separate ping result file at output/pings/{model}.txt using the exact structure and emoji shown here:

  🧪 PING {model-name}

  📤 Sent:     {HH:MM:SS.mmm}
  📥 Received: {HH:MM:SS.mmm}
  ⏱️  Latency:  {formatted-duration}

  🎯 Pong!

  Formatting rules for the duration:
  - < 1000ms: display as "XXXms" (rounded to nearest ms)
  - 1000ms–<60000ms: display as seconds with exactly 2 decimals, e.g., "1.33s"
  - ≥60000ms: display as minutes with exactly 2 decimals, e.g., "1.03min"
  Keep the blank lines exactly where shown.
- Then create a comparison file at output/comparison/compare_all.txt that ranks the compare list by fastest latency first, with this structure:

  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
  🧪 MODEL COMPARISON
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════

  🥇 {fastestModel}  {formatted-duration}
  🥈 {secondModel}  {formatted-duration}
  🥉 {thirdModel}   {formatted-duration}
  4️⃣  {fourthModel}  {formatted-duration}

  🏆 Fastest: {fastestModel} ({formatted-duration})

  You can add spaces for alignment as needed, but the order, medals, and durations must be correct. Use the same duration formatting rules above.
- Do not include any extra commentary in the files. Create directories as needed.

The input file content (also present at input/ping_scenarios.json) is:
{
  "single": [
    {"model": "kimi", "sent": "09:34:15.123", "received": "09:34:15.247"},
    {"model": "minimax", "sent": "10:02:05.000", "received": "10:02:06.333"},
    {"model": "gemini", "sent": "11:59:59.120", "received": "12:01:01.120"}
  ],
  "compare": {
    "models": [
      {"model": "kimi", "sent": "13:10:00.000", "received": "13:10:00.800"},
      {"model": "deepseek", "sent": "13:10:00.000", "received": "13:10:02.450"},
      {"model": "openai", "sent": "13:10:00.000", "received": "13:10:05.670"},
      {"model": "glm", "sent": "13:10:00.000", "received": "13:10:01.100"}
    ]
  }
}

Deliverables:
- output/pings/kimi.txt
- output/pings/minimax.txt
- output/pings/gemini.txt
- output/comparison/compare_all.txt
